article.headline: Illinois St. 83, Wichita St. 75
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. (AP) -- Levi Dyer was perfect from the line and behind the arc, finishing with 20 points as Illinois State beat Wichita State 83-75 Thursday night. Dyer hit 4-of-4 from the free throw line and from 3-point range, combining with Osiris Eldridge to sink seven of Illinois State's 3-pointers. Eldridge finished with 16 points for the Redbirds (10-9, 2-6 Missouri Valley). The Shockers (12-7, 3-5) got a game-high 27 points from Kyle Wilson. Wilson was 7-of-12 from the field, including 5-of-6 from 3-point range, and 8-of-10 from the free throw line before fouling out with 3:26 to go in the game. P.J. Couisnard added 15 points and Ryan Martin scored 14 for Wichita State, which got a game-high six boards apiece from each of them and Sean Ogirri. Illinois State built on a 34-29 halftime lead with 59 percent second-half shooting and finished at 54 percent, compared with the Shockers' 35 percent, for the game. Anthony Slack came off the bench to hit six of seven foul shots and finish with 14 points for the Redbirds.
